      "writtenOn": "2015-09-11T13:41:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please use a simpler API, nobody likes to do a string comparison to check a boolean, and a failure to read the flag should be interpreted as an opt-out. Just use something like:\n\n  // Try to find whether the user has agreed to send anonymized\n  // usage data to Android Studio servers. This works by\n  // parsing Android Studio configuration files created\n  // at install time. Returns true if the user agreed,\n  // false otherwise or if the files cannot be found.\n  bool android_studio_get_optins_flag(void);",
      "revId": "24f73e62c5fdc51d1e771ad0f3edef57aae1e577",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
