        "filename": "android/metrics/studio_helper.h",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 48,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-11T13:41:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Asking the user to provide an appropriately-sized buffer is generally a bad API, just return a heap-allocated C string instead, and use a \u0027bool\u0027 type for the return value if you don\u0027t need several error values, it\u0027s simpler, as in:\n\n  // Find the Android Studio installation ID and return\n  // it as a string. On success, return true and sets\n  // |*id| to point to a new heap-allocated string, which\n  // must be freed by the caller with free().\n  // On failure, return false.\n  bool android_studio_get_installation_id(char** id);\n\nOr you could use C++ and return and android::base::String or an std::string, which would be empty on error.",
      "revId": "24f73e62c5fdc51d1e771ad0f3edef57aae1e577",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
